Class Placement

  • java.lang.Object
    • greenmirror.Placement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CornerBottomLeftPlacement, CornerBottomRightPlacement, CornerTopLeftPlacement, CornerTopRightPlacement, CustomPlacement, EdgeBottomPlacement, EdgeLeftPlacement, EdgePlacement, EdgeRightPlacement, EdgeTopPlacement, MiddlePlacement, NoPlacement, RandomPlacement

    public abstract class Placement
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    The Placement abstract class used for indicating where a Node should be placed relative to another Node.

    If you want to use just the placement information, use the singleton Placement.SUBCLASS. E.g.: Placement.MIDDLE. If you want to use extra, relative position information, create a new instance of a subclass, like: new Placement.Middle(). The Custom subclass does not have a singleton, because extra, relative position information must be given.

    Author:
    Karim El Assal
